While angels watch the soft repose. 3 But, though earth's fairest blossoms die, 3 So Jesus slept; God's dying Son [bed! Dispel our cares, and chase our fears: Attend, o earth! his sovereign word; If God be ours, we're traveling home, Restore thy trust;-a glorious form Though passing through a vale of tears. Shall then arise to meet the Lord. MERIBAH. C. P. M. 1.
